- Title: Introducing Transformers.js: State-of-the-art Machine Learning From Your Browser
- Author: Hugging Face
- Date: Current release date
- Keywords: Machine Learning, Web Development, AI, Artificial Intelligence, Transformers.js, Browser-based, ONNX, Pytorch, TensorFlow, JAX, Audio, Computer Vision, Natural Language Processing
- Categories: Technology, Software
- Summary: Hugging Face introduces Transformers.js, which allows you to run transformer models directly in your browser, with no server required. The API supports tasks across natural language processing, computer vision, audio, and multimodal functionalities. ONNX Runtime is utilized for efficient in-browser execution of the models. Transformers.js is compatible with pretrained PyTorch, TensorFlow, or JAX models, which can be easily converted to ONNX using Hugging Face's Optimum. Check out Hugging Face's documentation for more information on using Transformers.js.
